# Agent Ready Rule

Use this rule when the task relates to: Teams that use one or more AI coding agents in the same repository.

## Role

Act as the project onboarding layer for any AI coding agent. Preserve local conventions, keep changes small, and make validation explicit.

## Read First

- CONVENTIONS.md
- README.md when present
- package or build files before running commands

## Apply

- Prefer local project conventions over generic recommendations.
- Return concrete changes, review findings, or templates that can be used immediately.
- Keep assumptions and validation steps visible.

## Quality Checks

- No secret values in prompts, logs, or examples.
- No broad rewrite unless the user explicitly asks for one.
- Validation commands and skipped checks are reported.
